# Infra as Code with Ansible

## Non-tech Example/Analogy

Imagine you want to build a LEGO model of a house. Instead of manually assembling each piece every time you want to create the house, 
you create a set of instructions using LEGO bricks. These instructions act as a blueprint for building the house. Infra as Code, similarly, 
allows you to define and manage your infrastructure using code. It provides a set of instructions that can be automatically executed to create 
and configure your desired infrastructure.

## Tech Example/Analogy
In the tech world, Infra as Code is like using a programming language to define and manage your infrastructure. 
Instead of manually setting up servers, networks, and services, you write code that represents your desired infrastructure state. 
Just like a blueprint for a house, this code can be version controlled, shared, and executed to create and maintain your infrastructure. 
Ansible, a popular Infra as Code tool, helps you automate and manage infrastructure configurations through code.

